contentrichtext.text: '''Tuckahoe''' may refer to [[Tuckahoe-Cohee]], an early American cultural sub-group. It may also refer to: ;Buildings: *[[Tuckahoe (Jensen Beach, Florida)]], or the Leach Mansion, in Jensen Beach, Florida *[[Tuckahoe Plantation]], boyhood home of Thomas Jefferson, in Virginia ;Bodies of water: *[[Tuckahoe Bay]], in South Carolina *[[Tuckahoe Creek]], in Maryland *[[Tuckahoe River (New Jersey)]] ;Places: *[[Tuckahoe, New Jersey]], an unincorporated community in Upper Township *[[Tuckahoe, Suffolk County, New York]], a hamlet in Suffolk County *[[Tuckahoe, Virginia]], a census-designated place in Henrico County *[[Tuckahoe (village), New York]], a village in Westchester County **[[Tuckahoe marble quarries]] **[[Tuckahoe (Metro-North station)]], railroad station *[[Tuckahoe State Park]], in Maryland ;Other uses: *[[Wolfiporia extensa]], also called ''Poria cocos'', '''Tuckahoe''', or '''Indian Bread'''; the sclerotium of a fungus used as food by Native Americans and by the Chinese as a medicinal *[[Camp Tuckahoe]], a Boy Scouts of America camp in Pennsylvania {{disambig}} [[Category:Place name disambiguation pages]]
